Package io.cyborgcode.roa.ui.insertion

Class BaseInsertionService<A extends Annotation>

All Implemented Interfaces:

Direct Known Subclasses:
InsertionServiceFieldImpl
public abstract class BaseInsertionService<A extends Annotation> extends Object implements InsertionService
Abstract base class for insertion services that handle inserting data into UI components.

This class defines a generic mechanism to process annotated fields in an object and insert corresponding values into the UI using registered insertion services.

Implementing classes must define specific behaviors for extracting field annotations, determining component types, building locators, and retrieving enum values.

  • Method Details

    • insertData

      public void insertData(Object data)
      Processes the provided data object, extracts annotated fields, and inserts values into corresponding UI components.

      The method:

      1. Retrieves all declared fields of the given object.
      2. Filters and sorts the fields based on the implementation logic.
      3. For each field:
        • Retrieves the annotation (if present).
        • Identifies the corresponding ComponentType.
        • Fetches the appropriate insertion service.
        • Builds the locator and retrieves the field value.
        • Performs pre-insertion operations (if any).
        • Invokes the insertion service to insert the value.
        • Performs post-insertion operations (if any).
      Specified by:
      insertData in interface InsertionService
      Parameters:
      data - The object containing values to be inserted into UI components.
      Throws:
      IllegalStateException - If no insertion service is found for a component type.
      RuntimeException - If field access fails.

      protected abstract int getOrder(A annotation)
      Determines the processing order for fields annotated with this service‚Äôs annotation.

      Fields with lower order values are processed before fields with higher values.

      Parameters:

      Returns:
      an integer representing the priority (lower means earlier)

      protected abstract Class<? extends ComponentType> getComponentTypeEnumClass(A annotation)

      This method is used to locate the specific enum type which defines the set of component types associated with the annotation. Implementations should inspect the annotation‚Äôs attributes to return the correct enum class.

      Parameters:

      Returns:
      the Class object of an enum that implements ComponentType

    • extractComponentTypeClass

      protected static Class<? extends ComponentType> extractComponentTypeClass(Class<? extends ComponentType> componentTypeClass)
      Resolves the specific interface that implements ComponentType from a given enum class.

      If the provided componentTypeClass directly implements ComponentType, it is returned immediately. Otherwise, this method inspects its interfaces and returns the first one that in turn extends ComponentType.

      Parameters:
      componentTypeClass - the enum class (or interface) to inspect for a ComponentType implementation
      Returns:
      the interface class which extends ComponentType
      Throws:
      IllegalStateException - if no interface extending ComponentType is found
